John F. Wallach et al., Appellants, v. Cornelius K. G. Billings et al. On Appeal of Pauline Cahn et al., Executors, v. Chicago National Bank et al., Appellees.Gen. No. 20,906.

(Not to be reported in ML)

Appeal from the Circuit Court of Cook county; the Hon. Lockwood Honor®, Judge, presiding.Heard in the Branch Appellate Court at the October term, 1914.Affirmed.Opinion filed December 21, 1915.

Statement of the Case.

Bill by John F. Wallach et al., complainants, against Cornelius K. G. Billings et al., defendants, on the appeal of Pauline Cahn et al., executors, against the Chicago National Bank et al., appellees.

A decree sustaining a general demurrer to the bill and dismissing the bill for want of equity affirmed on the authority of Wallach v. Billings, Gen. No. 20,733, ante, p. 605.

Foreman, Levin & Robertson, for appellants.Sears, Meagher & Whitney for appellee Cornelius K. G. Billings; Nathaniel C. Sears, James F. Meagherand Jesse J. Ricks, of counsel. Mr. Justice Barnes

delivered the opinion of the court.
